From paboyoun at fhcrc.org  Tue Oct 21 23:57:47 2008
From: paboyoun at fhcrc.org (Patrick Aboyoun)
Date: Tue, 21 Oct 2008 14:57:47 -0700
Subject: [Bioc-devel] BioC 2.3 SVN BRANCH TO BE CREATED,
 PLEASE REFRAIN FROM SVN SUBMITS UNTIL 6PM PDT
Message-ID: <48FE505B.3080502@fhcrc.org>

I am happy to announce that we are getting really close to the BioC 2.3 
release. In order to prepare for this release, all developers *must* 
refrain from SVN commits until further notification, which will be at or 
before 6 pm PDT - roughly 3 hours from now. This check in moratorium is 
needed because we need to create a branch in SVN to hold the BioC 2.3 
code line and your check-ins could inadvertently cause your package to 
break become the files may not wind up in the SVN repository that you 
intended it to. Thanks for your help on this matter.


Patrick


